<SLUG> BC-HALL-HALLMARK-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DON HALL JR. BECOMES HALLMARK CORPORATE VICE PRESIDENT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JENNIFER MANN  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Hallmark Cards Inc. has promoted Don Hall
Jr., grandson of company founder Joyce C. Hall, to the new position
of corporate vice president of strategy and development.
</P>
<P>
   He will be accountable for developing Hallmark's vision and
growth strategy.
</P>
<P>
   Hall, 43, joined Hallmark in 1975 and has worked in a variety of
positions. Most recently, he was vice president of product
development. He will report to Irvine O. Hockaday Jr., 62, chief
executive officer of Hallmark.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don will be working closely with me on long-term growth
strategy for our overall business,'' Hockaday said. ``He also will
be working with the presidents of each of our businesses on the
creation of strategic business plans and opportunities for
synergy.''
</P>
<P>
   Hall holds a bachelor's degree in economics and literature from
Claremont College in Claremont, Calif., and an MBA from the
University of Kansas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
