<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Infiniti I30 gives luxury real meaning
 &HT;    By Linda Sharp
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ In any field, a few wonders occasionally rise _ things
or situations that have no reasonable explanation.
</P>
<P>
   The Infiniti I30 might fall into that category in the automotive
arena.
</P>
<P>
   The I30 is a really nice car. It's comfortable and offers a
silky smooth drive to the entry-level luxury market. At 227
horsepower and 217 pounds-feet of torque on the 2000 model, it
offers one of the most potent powerplants available in the
under-$35,000 luxury segment.
</P>
<P>
   So why doesn't the brand make any noise? The I30's 3.0-liter V-6
has been named one of the 10 best engines by Ward's Auto World for
five consecutive years. When the model was introduced in 1995,
Kiplinger's Personal Finance declared the I30 the best new car in
the $25,000-$35,000 price range. In 1996, IntellicChoice lauded the
I30 as having the lowest maintenance costs in its class.
</P>
<P>
   J.D. Power and Associates recognized the I30 in its 1997 Initial
Quality Study as best in class. Kiplinger's continued to applaud
the I30 in '98, voting it best in the $25,000-$35,000 class. And
Infiniti has a strong record of reliability.
</P>
<P>
   The number of vintage Datsun/Nissan products I see daily on the
roadways intrigues me. There appears to be a continuing presence of
510s, Sentras, 200 SXs, Pulsars and Maximas.
</P>
<P>
   Sales of the I30 were up 20 percent for the '99 model year, and
Infiniti acknowledges the I30 was one of its most valuable players.
Infiniti is set to begin capitalizing on the I30's increased sales
strength with the introduction of the 2000 model I30.
</P>
<P>
   Infiniti's parent company, Nissan Motor Corp., recently got a
capital investment by French automaker Renault, which should
provide the financial foundation for all of Nissan's product lines
to grow.
</P>
<P>
   Along with its nearly 20 percent increase in power, the 2000 I30
will also get a retuned rear suspension, Xenon headlamps, advanced
traction control system, more-sensitive anti-lock brakes, larger
wheels and tires, and a standard 200-watt Bose audio system.
Enhanced safety features include a new head-restraint system
designed to reduce whiplash.
</P>
<P>
   A timely new feature will be the availability of a
power-operated rear sunshade, which tests have indicated can
provide nine-degree reduction in cabin temperatures.
</P>
<P>
   Infiniti also will offer the Infiniti Communicator, which uses
cell phone technology and the Global Positioning Satellite system
to provide emergency and roadside assistance along with general
travel services.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
