A1788 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-DISNEYLAND-GO-LADN     08-10 0227
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DISNEYLAND-GO-LADN </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
IF YOU GO
<TEXT>
<P>
   COSTS: Disneyland admission is $39 for adults, $29 for children
ages 3 to 11, $37 for seniors ages 60 and up. Two- and three-day
passports are available. Parking is $7, $8 for RVs (overnight
parking is not permitted).
</P>
<P>
   HOURS: During the summer, the park is open from 8 a.m. until
midnight. Disneyland goes to a shorter schedule after Labor Day
weekend.
</P>
<P>
   WHAT'S NEW: Tarzan's Treehouse recently opened in Adventureland.
It replaces the Swiss Family Robinson Treehouse _ and bears a
striking resemblance to the old attraction. In fact, you're left to
wonder if they simply changed the sign out front. Little ones
hooked on the movie will love it, though; there's an interactive
area at the base of the tree. Tomorrowland has been refurbished,
but you'll wonder if the designers did nothing more than give
everything a coat of paint, move the rocket jets a few hundred feet
and add the Rocket Rods, an attraction which runs on the old People
Mover track and has been subject to chronic breakdowns.
</P>
<P>
   INFORMATION: For directions through the construction projects at
and around Disneyland, and for such helpful information as each
day's scheduled ride closures, phone (714) 781-4560;
Web: &UR;  &LR; www.disney.go.com/disneyland &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
