<P>
   On its fifth anniversary, The New York Times Syndicate's New
America News Service, the source of the foremost voices of
diversity, is being revamped and revitalized.
</P>
<P>
   New America is a special wire service dedicated to stories that
reflect our nation's varied social and ethnic makeup.
</P>
<P>
   Having attended Unity '99, we understand the needs of editors
across the nation who are on the hunt for topnotch multicultural
material for their publications.
</P>
<P>
   ---We believe New America News Service is the answer.---
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE HIGHLIGHTS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ NEWS-DRIVEN COMMENTARIES FROM A STELLAR LINEUP OF WRITERS,
INCLUDING: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LISA LING, correspondent for the ABC TV show ``The View.''
</P>
<P>
   MARCIA GILLESPIE, editor in chief of Ms. magazine.
</P>
<P>
   JAMES GARCIA, editor and publisher of Politico, the first
national weekly newsletter focusing on U.S. Latino politics.
Formerly the editor in chief of the San Antonio Current. President
of the Austin Association of Hispanic Journalists.
</P>
<P>
   VERNON JARRETT, former columnist for Chicago Sun Times and one
of the city's most highly respected commentators. Jarrett is an
active member of the National Advisory Board of the Rosa and
Raymond Parks Pathways to Freedom Programs for Youths. In 1991 he
received the National Association of Black Journalists' Lifetime
Achievement Award.
</P>
<P>
   JUAN GONZALEZ, a staff columnist for The New York Daily News
since 1988.
</P>
<P>
   TIM GIAGO, president and publisher of Giago Book Publishing.
</P>
<P>
   CHUCK COLBERT, who serves on the board of directors of the
National Lesbian and Gay Journalists Association.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ CELEBRITY GUEST WRITERS. &LR;  Each month, we invite an
outstanding individual to pen an 800-word commentary on a pressing
issue in the headlines.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ SELECTIONS FROM A VARIETY OF ETHNIC PUBLICATIONS, &LR;  including
Hispanic magazine, Hispanic Business, A. magazine and KoreAm.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ MONTHLY BOOK EXCERPTS FROM NOTED AUTHORS OF COLOR. &LR;  First up:
three excerpts from Juliette Fairley's ``Money Talks,'' a how-to
tome geared toward African-Americans that offers tips on saving and
investing as we enter the new millennium.
</P>
