   BARRACE _ WASHINGTON _ Republican Rep. Bob Barr boasts a
half-million dollars in the bank and a national base of
contributors in his race for a fourth term in Congress. Barr's
contributors stretch from south Florida to Seattle and include Guy
Millner, former Gov. Lester Maddox, Post Properties chairman John
A. Williams and House Republican Whip Tom DeLay's PAC. But Roger
Kahn, the only Democrat raising money to run against Barr, has more
than $200,000 and impressive donor's list of his own. Kahn counts
