 CHRON  
 Editors note: Psst! Read the latest? If not, you haven't read
Hot  Stuff, the San Francisco Chronicle's weekly roundup of great
new 
 home-and-garden items and places to visit.   HOT STUFF: Home Accessories Get Wired  
   
   
 SAN FRANCISCO _ Distinctive Designs ' wiry, delicate-looking
objects may appear to be full of air, but they actually hold a wide
range of household items.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Veena Santhiogoset of San Francisco got the idea for her beaded
wire baskets during a wire-sculpting class. ``She picked it up in
one day,'' remembers her husband, Steven Reinhold. ``We brought
some of the items to a gift fair and the business went from nothing
into something overnight.''
</P>
<P>
   The husband-and-wife team's repertoire now includes the pictured
champagne bucket ($57), with a plastic insert for holding ice, and
short and tall wine holders, in copper and black wire ($22 to $28).
</P>
<P>
   Other Distinctive Designs pieces include jewellike lanterns ($64
to $140), large covered breadbaskets ($75 to $108) and fanciful
night lights ($40 to $55).
</P>
<P>
   The unique spiral wire and beaded designs are also incorporated
in handmade wood furniture and accessories. The ``Millennium End
Tables'' ($325) feature inner halogen lights that shine through
large colored beads embedded in the wood.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  The Distinctive Designs studio is open from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. &LR; 
 &LR; Monday through Friday or by appointment. 3259 Mission St., &LR; 
 &LR; second floor, San Francisco, (415) 647-2131. You can also find &LR; 
 &LR; the products at Zia Houseworks, 1310 10th St., Berkeley, (510) &LR; 
 &LR; 528-2377; Spirals, 367 University Ave., Palo Alto, (650) &LR; 
 &LR; 324-1155; Cottonworks, (408) 395-9224, 58 N. Santa Cruz Ave., &LR; 
 &LR; Los Gatos; or through the Sundance Catalog, (800) 422-2770. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR;   &LR; _ Tara Duggan, San Francisco Chronicle
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
