 CHRON  
 Editors note: The San Francisco Chronicle rounds up the best
of  the unusual for home and garden in this regular feature, Off
the 
 Wall.   OFF THE WALL: Do-It-All Recliner Has You Sitting Down on the Job  
   
 By Tara Duggan  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
   
SAN FRANCISCO _ With their enveloping padding and almost horizontal
recliners, you may think that La-Z-Boys were already as
comfortable, not to mention impossible to get out of, as they could
be.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Well, you're wrong. The maker of this classic icon of American
comfort and domestic fashion is making sure that you will never
leave your chair _ ever _ again. The new Maxim La-Z-Boy offers all
the comfort of your favorite chair plus all the convenience of your
office.
</P>
<P>
   But let there be no confusion here. This chair isn't for working
from home, it's for enjoying the game in the best way possible.
Armchair-quarterback owners of the Maxim ($760) can screen phone
calls, order pizza on a speaker phone, get a soothing massage when
the opposing team wins and hook up to the Web to check scores on
other games. Of course, there are also compartments for a TV
directory book  &LR; and a favorite beverage.
</P>
<P>
   Coming out in stores next month, La-Z-Boy takes the inevitable
next step with Oasis ($899). This beauty has all the features of
the Maxim, but in lieu of a modem hookup there's a built-in cooler
that just happens to be big enough to hold a six-pack.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
WHERE TO FIND IT
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; La-Z-Boys are available at La-Z-Boy Furniture Galleries,
Montgomery Ward and other furniture outlets. Call (800) 625-3246 or
visit  &LR; www.lazboy.com &LR;  to find the nearest location. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
