These are the stories The San Francisco Chronicle Home section
plans to move Tuesday, Aug. 10, on the New York Times News Service
wire. Questions? Please call Holly Ocasio Rizzo at 415-777-8811. &HT;      San Francisco _ LAWN _  New lawns face a tough test: Ali
Harivandi's test. For 20 years, the environmental horticulturist
has planted, nurtured and coaxed grass seeds to sprout at trial
plots in Santa Clara. Then he has examined and cross-examined them
to judge the best grasses for Bay Area lawns.
 &HT;    Turf experts such as Harivandi, who works for the University of
California Cooperative Extension Service in Hayward, are
responsible for an explosion of new varieties of grasses that can
withstand kids, dogs, heat and drought. And, as grass becomes
stronger, it is also acquiring a new aesthetic _ still the green
frame around a house, but also studded with low-growing wildflowers
and mowed in naturalistic patterns.
 &HT;    With optional sidebars: varieties to plant, Care and feeding,
pests and remedies, lawn-mower racing, where to learn more. 
 By Holly Ocasio Rizzo  
