.
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
on the Jewish Community Center shooting for use by NYTimes News
Service clients as available. For questions about stories, please
contact Lisa Girion at the Daily News, (818) 713-3707. &QL; 
. &QL; 
SHOOTING (Los Angeles) _ A teenaged suspect opened fire in the
lobby of a Jewish Community Center in the north San Fernando
Valley, wounding three young boys, a teenage counselor and a
teacher. One boy is in very critical condition. The suspect armed
with a 9 mm Uzi got away after spraying the lobby with 30-40
bullets. By Harrison Sheppard. (Will move in the ``n'' state and
``a'' national news files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
PARENTS (Los Angeles) _ Panicked parents sped to the Jewish
Community Center in Granada Hills on word of the shooting to fetch
their children. Parents were directed next door to a church shared
by Temple Beth Torah, a command post where police and daycare
workers were taking children and reuniting them with family
members. By Sherry Joe Crosby. (Will move in the ``n'' state and
``a'' national news files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
VICTIMS (Los Angeles) _ Profiles of victims, who include three boys
and two women. By Mike Coit. (Will move in the ``n'' state and
``a'' national news files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
TRIP (Los Angeles) _ Most of the 200 children who attend school or
daycare at the North Valley Jewish Community Center missed the
mayhem because they were on a field trip to the Museum of Tolerance
in West Los Angeles. By Douglas Haberman. (Will move in the ``n''
state and ``a'' national news files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
SECURITY (Los Angeles) _ At the West Valley Jewish Community
Center, children were sent home early. At other daycare centers and
preschools in the Los Angeles area, children were kept inside, door
locks were checked and directors kept their fingers on panic
buttons. Parks throughout the region got increased security as a
massive police and fire paramedic response was mounted. By Troy
Anderson. (Will move in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news
files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
PSYCH (Los Angeles) _ It's a parent's worst nightmare, a shooting
at your child's day care center. Just imagine what it's like for a
young child _ the sounds of gunshots, people screaming, being
snatched from your home away from home. How do children view these
events and how can parents help their children make sense of this?
By Phil Davis. (Will move in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national
news files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
NEIGHBORHOOD _ The neighborhood around the North Valley Jewish
Community Center has been in the national media spotlight before.
When the Northridge Earthquake rocked the San Fernando Valley, a
gasline blew up underneath nearby Balboa Boulevard, destroying four
homes and creating an open gas fire that was one of the defining
images of the temblor. A month later, as the residents began the
long rebuilding of their neighborhood, President Clinton and
statewide and local politicians toured the neighborhood, standing a
few hundred yards from the community center and declaring that the
Valley was on the road to recovery. By Dominic Berbeo. (Will move
in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
OFFICIAL _ Reaction to the shooting from Mayor Richard Riordan,
council members and other officials. By Dominic Berbeo and Deborah
Sullivan. (Will move in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news
files.) &QL;
</P>
