   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ The government and Microsoft
lay out their presentations of what they regard as the facts in the
antitrust case _their legal effort to sway the judge's ultimate
findings. By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   UPS-TAX (Undated) _ United Parcel Service said on Tuesday that a
Tax Court ruling that it used a Bermuda company to create phony tax
deductions in 1984 will cost it $300 million in taxes, penalties
and interest for just that one year if the decision stands on
appeal. The company said it had no estimate of its potential
liability for back taxes over the next 13 years. By David Cay
Johnston.
</P>
