<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKN-WRIGHT _ ATLANTA _ Lorenzen Wright can attribute most of his
success as a basketball player to his father Herb, a former college
and pro basketball player during his youth. The elder Wright began
to have a huge impact on his son's life in an unusual way - after
surviving a shooting incident which left him paralyzed from the
waist down, Herb ended his pro career and began the day-to-day
challenge of helping his son develop as a player and a person. With
his father by his side, Wright became the newest Atlanta Hawk over
the weekend. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NASCAR-RACISM _ NASCAR suspends two crew members after one
put a sheet over his head _ Ku Klux Klan style _ during an argument
with black crew member of another race team. Top NASCAR drivers and
officials say the sport _ already labeled as racist in some corners
_ cannot afford similar incidents. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
