<P>
   RUSSIA-FIGHTING _ MOSCOW _ In his first full day as Russia's
latest prime minister, Vladimir Putin was summoned to the Kremlin
by President Boris Yeltsin to devise a plan to avert a broader war
with Islamic militants in the southern border region. Muslim
geurrillas declared Russia's Dagestan republic a independent state
on Tuesday and called for a holy war against the Moscow-aligned
government. The fighting is Russia's worst security crisis since
the disasterous, two-year war in nearby Chechnya, which ended in
1996. (Holmes, Cox News Service).
