A2272 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      08-10 0553
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release WEDNESDAY AMs, August   11, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-MILITANTS (Moscow) _ Islamic militants greet Vladimir
Putin by declaring an independent republic in Dagestan. Putin vows
to return the area to normalcy as a Russian military buildup sets
up the biggest confrontation since the 1994-96 Chechnya fiasco. By
David Filipov. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-TERRORIST (Tel Aviv) _ New Prime Minister Ehud Barak
responds with restraint after a Palestinian rams his car into
hitchhiking Israeli soldiers, injuring 12 before being shot to
death by the troops. By Aliza Marcus. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   EICHMANN-PAPERS (Tel Aviv) _ Israel decides, after pressure from
Adolph Eichmann's son, to release 1,300 pages of a manuscript by
the former top Nazi. By Aliza Marcus. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RACE-RULING (Boston) _ Federal Judge Nancy Gertner decides
Boston's race-based student assignment plan can't be ended easily
before school begins, but should be abolished in time for school in
September 2000. By Beth Daley. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MYSTERY-DEATH (Undated) _ In a mystery authorities are trying to
unravel, David Coughlin of Massachusetts is found dead in Carlsbad
Caverns National Park, his longtime friend Raffi Kodikian, sitting
next to his grave. By Yvonne Abraham and Carold Monje Jr. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   AIR-RAGE (Boston) _ Miami resident Patricia Lemerise will defend
herself Wednesday on criminal charges that stem, she believes, from
just one fact: That she used the f-word on an airplane. By Joanna
Weiss. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   FISH-COMEBACK (Boston) _ Many of New England's fishing stocks,
