unravel, David Coughlin of Massachusetts is found dead in Carlsbad
Caverns National Park, his longtime friend Raffi Kodikian, sitting
next to his grave. By Yvonne Abraham and Carold Monje Jr. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   AIR-RAGE (Boston) _ Miami resident Patricia Lemerise will defend
herself Wednesday on criminal charges that stem, she believes, from
just one fact: That she used the f-word on an airplane. By Joanna
Weiss. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   FISH-COMEBACK (Boston) _ Many of New England's fishing stocks,
once on the brink of collapse, appear to be on the mend, fisheries
scientists say. By Karen Hsu. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ICUBE-RAZORFISH (Undated) _ I-Cube is sold to Razorfish for
stock worth about $677 million, a big figure for two companies few
know. But their executives say they've got an old-fashioned
business model: Sell internet services for more than they cost to
provide. By Ross Kerber. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSING-ACTIVIST (Boston) _ Self-styled housing guerrilla Bruce
Marks seals a landmark deal with the nation's largest bank to
channel $3 billion in affordable mortgages through his Boston
organization. By Lynnley Browning. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   COPLEY-TEVA (Boston) _ Copley Pharmaceuticals, trying to recover
from a drug-manufacturing scandal, is acquired by Teva
Pharmaceutical, Israel's largest drug maker, for $220 milion in
cash. By Ronald Rosenberg. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Smithfield, R.I.) -- The Patriots are so banged up
that they're holding auditions, bringing in veteran linebacker
Steven Morrison, formerly of the Indianapolis Colts, and former
Tampa Bay running back and special teams player Jerry Ellison. By
Nick Cafardo. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-ROYALS (Kansas City) _ By Gordon Edes.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
