<P>
   &UR; TO HELL AND BACK &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FOUR COLOR SLIDES ARE AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; (1,200 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By KEVIN KRAJICK &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Four scientists wearing coveralls enter an elevator that plunges
hundreds of stories down into the darkness _ No. 5 Shaft in South
Africa's East Driefontein gold mine. The goal: to find living
microbes that eat and breathe geologic ingredients such as iron,
manganese and sulfur. Kevin Krajick is a reporter for Discover
magazine.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-MICROBES-IN-EARTH-NYTSF. Sent to category codes
