 &UR; THREE COLOR SLIDES ARE AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; (1,000 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By KAREN WRIGHT &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Karen Wright, a contributing editor to Discover magazine,
reports on the semiannual pupfish count in Ash Meadows, Nev., a
24,000-acre oasis of clay dunes, spring-fed pools, and plants and
animals found nowhere else in the world.
</P>
<P>
