<P>
   KOSOVO-OUTLOOK (Pristina, Yugoslavia) _ The U.N. mission in
Kosovo is finally moving to establish its authority here as the
province's government, to try to fill the vacuum exploited by the
Kosovo Liberation Army. Senior U.N. officials admit that they are
now in a period of testing with the KLA, but they are also eager
not to drive the army into opposition. To that end, says Bernard
Kouchner, the chief U.N. administrator in Kosovo, he wants to pull
the KLA and and others into the exercise of power and will offer to
provide them a share of executive responsibility as quickly as
possible. By Steven Erlanger. (We plan to move the story by 8 p.m.
ET in ``i'' news file.) 2,000 words.
