<P>
   OPEN-AIR-MOVIES (Baltimore) _ After the sun has set, 89-year-old
John Pente beams down upon the fresh life that has come to the
aging streets of his beloved Little Italy: An al fresco specialty
from the Old Country, open-air movies, flash onto the parking lot
wall of Da Mimmo's restaurant, projected from a bedroom window of
Pente's row house. In the street, hundreds of people gather with
their lawn chairs for the free showings, silent but for the movie
dialogue and the audience's lip-smacking at the gift cannolis from
Vaccaro's bakery. By Francis X. Clines. (The story has moved in
``a'' news file.) 1,000 words.
