   GAYS-POLITICS (Washington) _ The statements of George W. Bush,
Elizabeth Dole and John McCain about homosexuals signals a
softening of the Republican positions on this subject but alarms
some conservatives in the party. By Katharine Q. Seelye. (The story
has moved in ``a'' news file.) 1,900 words.
</P>
<P>
   PARAGUAY-ARCHIVE (Asuncion, Paraguay) _ When Martin Almada asked
a judge for records of his arrest under the dictatorship of Gen.
Alfredo Stroessner, he hoped merely to learn more about his own
private misery: nearly four years of captivity under torture.
Instead, the one-time school teacher unearthed a mountain of
records detailing repression among U.S.-backed military regimes
throughout South America during the Cold War. By Diana Jean Schemo.
(The story has moved in ``i'' news file.) 2,000 words.
