   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SPORTS-MINORITIES (Houston) _ More than 52 years after
baseball legend Jackie Robinson cracked the pro sports color line,
minorities have barely penetrated top ranks of the industry,
according to National League President Leonard Coleman. Coleman
says there are not enough minorities in the executive offices of
teams. By LORI RODRIGUEZ. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RICKY'S-DAD (Houston) _ Errick Lynne Williams Sr., the
father of Heisman Trophy winner and New Orleans Saints running back
Ricky Williams, pleads guilty to third-degree felony theft and is
placed on 10 years deferred-adjudication probation by state
District Judge Mark Kent Ellis. The father of the famous back stole
more than $20,000 from a local nursing home in a bogus payroll
scheme. By STEVE BREWER.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Atlanta) _ The Houston Astros, 69-45, try to avenge
Monday night's 5-3 loss to the Atlanta Braves with a game tonight
in Atlanta. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
