<P>
   UNDATED _ Texas writer Jerry Flemmons once wrote: ``Of the
world's four great cuisines _ French, Italian, Chinese and Texan _
only the latter has a recipe beginning, `First, dig a 3-foot-deep
hole. ...' '' Flemmons was speaking of a skimpy, Texas backyard
barbecue, of course, not a cookout like the one in Dalhart this
weekend. It is there, high in the Texas Panhandle, that the XIT
Rodeo and Reunion takes place each August. This was the 63rd
reunion and, as usual, more than 20,000 free barbecue meals were
handed out. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
