<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-PERKINS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The world of jocks and nerds, preppies and geeks has
long defined high-school life on the screen and off. But it took a
murderous assault in a Denver suburb to shed light on the harmful
fallout of cliques, the teen-age alienation and anger that can
often result from strutting jocks and imperious prom queens who
lord over high schools like earthly gods. TV critic Ken Parish
Perkins reports on the slew of new series set in high schools. By
KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
