</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) NEW YORK -- Aug. 10, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., AUG. 15 --
PURE-POP-THEATER-2, 08-10 -- Starting Wednesday, the new Pure Pop
Festival, led by Aaron Beall, will go head to head with the
three-year-old Fringe Festival. ``Nobody's saying to Lincoln
Center, 'Hey, too many festivals, guys!' `` says Beall. ``Too much
creativity! You've got to stop it! Why do you need the Mozart? You
just did Schubert! Enough with the Mendelssohn!'' (Chester Higgins
Jr./New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
