1961. Israel announced on Tuesday that it would release Eichmann's
jailhouse memoirs, which have been kept under wraps in Israel's
national archives since his execution in 1962. The Justice Ministry
said the 1,300 pages, in which Eichmann tries to portray himself as
a mid-level official who only followed Hitler's orders, would be
released at the ``earliest opportunity'' in a scholarly fashion,
with background and commentary. (Israeli Government/New York Times
