<HEADER>
A2668 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ATL-SHOOTINGVICTIMS-C     08-10 0307
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ATL-SHOOTINGVICTIMS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Two Buckhead shooting victims out of hospital
 &HT;    By Stacy Shelton
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Two more Buckhead shooting victims were released from
the hospital Tuesday, and the last memorial service for one of the
nine killed has been scheduled Saturday outside St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   Kathy Vancamp and Scott Manspeaker, both employees at All-Tech
Investment Group, went home Tuesday after spending 12 nights at St.
Joseph's Hospital. Four more victims remain in other hospitals.
</P>
<P>
   The memorial service is for Scott Webb, 30, a day trader who was
shot at Momentum Securities in Piedmont Center. His body was
cremated. The 2 p.m. Saturday service will be at St. Peter's
Episcopal Church in Ladue, Mo., preceded by visiting hours from 10
a.m. to 1 p.m. at the Ortman-Stipanovich Funeral Home in Creve
Coeur, Mo.
</P>
<P>
   Vancamp, 38, lost her sight and will have to undergo about a
year's worth of plastic surgery, said family friend Roel Lopez. The
bullet caused entrance and exit wounds in her temple, and a second
gunshot to her chest damaged a lung and intestines, he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's going to have to go to school for vision impairment,
learn how to read Braille,'' Lopez said. Vancamp and her husband,
Michael Sovereign, will have to make changes to their home so she
can more easily get around.
</P>
<P>
   ``She wants to go back to work but we don't know whether she'll
be able to go back to work,'' Lopez said.
</P>
<P>
   Sovereign and Lopez have set up a fund in Vancamp's name to help
pay costs for her rehabilitation and schooling. Donations can be
made to the Kathy Vancamp Vision Fund at NationsBank branches.
</P>
<P>
   Manspeaker, 27, is expected to fully recover. He was shot in the
abdomen and right forearm.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
