<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-BROWNS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cowboys find positives among newcomers in OT defeat
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WICHITA FALLS, Texas _ If the choices are oral surgery or losing
a football game, Jerry Jones gladly will accept dental work.
</P>
<P>
   Still, the Dallas Cowboys' owner flashed a hopeful smile after
Monday night's 20-17 overtime loss to the Cleveland Browns in the
Hall of Fame game. Jones saw a glimpse of the future, and some of
the players whom the Cowboys gambled on this year were better than
advertised.
</P>
<P>
   Jones singled out linebacker Dat Nguyen, receivers Wane McGarity
and MarTay Jenkins, offensive lineman Solomon Page and defensive
end Ebenezer Ekuban.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nobody likes to lose, of course, but I liked what I saw in our
first- and second-year players,'' said Jones, who takes a hands-on
approach to the draft. ``We liked what we saw in the offensive
line. Troy (Aikman) looked like he had all the time in the world to
throw the football.''
</P>
<P>
   McGarity, a former Texas Longhorn, and Jenkins have had good
summer camps, and they extended their progress to the team's first
preseason game. They combined for four catches, 80 yards and one
touchdown. Neither dropped a pass.
</P>
<P>
   ``There were some good things that happened to this football
team (in the game),'' running back Emmitt Smith said. ``At the same
time, there were a lot of mistakes. Now that we have a game under
our belts, we can practice on correcting those mistakes.''
</P>
<P>
   Aikman and backup Jason Garrett paced an offense that passed for
270 yards, but the Cowboys, who boast about offensive balance, had
only 87 yards on the ground. The only effective running back was
Chris Warren, who showed some burst while running for 21 yards on
four carries.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman showed as much rust as anybody. His early fumble set up
Cleveland's first touchdown. He later threw an interception in the
end zone to kill another drive. The Cowboys did not score when
Aikman was in the game.
</P>
<P>
   The expansion Browns finished with 373 yards of total offense,
but most of those yards came after the starting unit left the game.
Rookie linemen Peppi Zellner and Ekuban rushed Cleveland passers Ty
Detmer and Tim Couch well at times. Nguyen, a former Texas A&AMP;M
standout who called defensive plays when he entered the game early,
had five tackles and sacked Couch with a vicious hit to the chest.
</P>
<P>
   Jones hopes this year's draft becomes a turning point for a
franchise that has been criticized for its draft in recent seasons.
Ekuban and Page, the first and second picks, were expected to do
well. But Jones said the Cowboys will receive a bonus if Nguyen,
McGarity, Zellner and Jenkins _ players taken after the second
round _ continue to make progress.
</P>
<P>
   ``In our division, Arizona and the (New York) Giants are going
to be better,'' Jones said, ``but I think we're going to be better,
too,'' Jones said of the NFC East, ``We had never swept the
division (8-0 record) until last season, and we feel we've improved
in some areas. We have a better pass rush, we're better in the
middle. The addition of (veteran defensive lineman) Alonzo Spellman
will help, too.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys, who return to training camp at 4 p.m. today, will
play their second preseason game Sunday afternoon in Oakland.
</P>
<P>
   Rick Cantu writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
